'''Kolpik''' is a type of traditional headgear worn in families of many [[Chassidic]] [[Rebbes]], by unmarried children on [[Shabbat]] and by Rebbes on special occasions.

it is a made from brown fur, as opposed to a [[spodik]], worn by polish [[chassidic]] dynasties, which is fashioned out of black fur.
